break4="sing."
english="She was just singing"}}
<p>Imperfective aspect describes events in progress and not complete.  It's used in all tenses and is usually added as a suffix to the tense it refers to.  The exceptions are present tense, which is unmarked, instead using the marker ra (if the preceding word ends with a vowel) or ta (if the preceding word ends in a consosant) and the future tense, whose marker has two morae, with ra after after the morae.  Otherwise, the imperfective aspect marker with the vowel and tone matching due to vowel harmony. Refer to the table below.</p>

